<p class="p2" style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial; -webkit-text-stroke-color: #000000;"><span class="s1" style="font-kerning: none; font-size: 14pt;">Digital accessibility covers existing and new software, electronic and information content, existing and new procurements, classroom deliverables, virtual meeting spaces, and other online activities.</span></p>
<p class="p2" style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial; -webkit-text-stroke-color: #000000;"><span class="s1" style="font-kerning: none; font-size: 14pt;">For more information, see the <a href="https://www.vpaa.uillinois.edu/cms/One.aspx?portalId=420456&amp;pageId=1550005" target="_blank">University of Illinois System's Electronic Information Technology (EIT) Accessibility Policy Guide</a>.</span></p>            </div>
